        content: {
          intro: `If you're replacing a 15-year-old furnace and AC in Phoenix and someone tries to sell you a new gas furnace paired with a new split-system air conditioner, ask them one question: "Did you run a Manual J?" If the answer is no — or a blank stare — walk away. They're not sizing your system; they're moving inventory. Here's the honest comparison between heat pumps and traditional furnace+AC systems in the Phoenix Valley, from someone who's installed hundreds of both.`,
